HEADWORD: Spadefoot
<hw>Spade"foot`</hw> <pr>(sp⟦amac⟧d"f⟦oocr⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any species of burrowing toads of the genus
<gen>Scaphiopus</gen>, esp. <spn>Scaphiopus Holbrookii</spn>, of the
Eastern United States; -- called also <altname>spade
toad</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spadeful</ent>⟦br⟧
